<item>
            <title>[ISS-532] A mistake in the documentation</title>
                <link>http://jira.perfect.org:8080/browse/ISS-532</link>
                <project id="10007" key="ISS">Issues</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the documentation of threading in&#160;the address: &lt;a href=&quot;http://example.com/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://perfect.org/docs/thread.html&lt;/a&gt;&#160;where the strategy of&#160;threading events is&#160;outlined, it is mentioned that after acquiring lock, a consumer should check if any&#160;resource is available to consume or calls&#160;&lt;ins&gt;wait()&lt;/ins&gt; otherwise.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Imagine&#160;there is a blocked consumer thread which&#160;called wait() on itself. Producer creates a resource, calls &lt;ins&gt;signal()&lt;/ins&gt; and releases the lock. another new incoming thread grabs the lock and consumes the newly created resource while the&#160;blocked thread receives signal and starts working in the hope of accessing&#160;a&#160;resource which doesn&apos;t exist anymore.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
